NAME

Test::Builder::SubtestSelection - Select subtests by name or by number

DESCRIPTION

This subclass of the "Test::Builder" class allows you to select subtests by
name or by number before running them. In your test script you have to use the
subclass before your test builder based testing framework. At the command-line
"prove" runs your test script and the subtest selection is based on the value
given to the "--subtest" option.

INSTALLATION

To install this module manually, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc
command.

    perldoc Test::Builder::SubtestSelection

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Test-Builder-SubtestSelection

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Test-Builder-SubtestSelection

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/Test-Builder-SubtestSelection


